cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PL 

This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it presents a high performance object store connector for Apache Spark, which is a distributed computing framework. It may also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories as it deals with object store semantics and performance testing. Additionally, it could be classified under Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories as it involves the implementation of a new connector and open source sharing.
